value.value: Mesenchyme of the digit region.
The collection of all skeletal elements in an forelimb zeugopod region.

label.value: parenchyma of quadrate lobe of liver

value.value: A liver parenchyma that is part of a quadrate lobe of liver.

label.value: parenchyma of caudate lobe of liver

value.value: A liver parenchyma that is part of a caudate lobe of liver.
An organism subdivision that includes both an appendage and its associated girdle region. Note that this includes both the skeletal elements and associated tissues (integument, muscle, etc).
Appendage girdle complex that when present, encompasses the pectoral appendicular skeleton and the pectoral girdle.
Appendage girdle complex that when present, encompasses the pelvic appendicular skeleton and the pelvic girdle.

Paired fin skeleton that consists of the supporting endochondral proximal and distal radials and the dermal fins rays or lepidotrichia. The pectoral fin skeleton is located in the thoracic region of the body and articulates with the scapula and coracoid.
Paired fin skeleton located in the abdominal position that consists of supporting endochondral radialsB and dermal fin rays or lepidotrichia.
Skeletal subdivision that is a segment of the limb skeleton.
The collection of all skeletal elements in a single paired fin.
An iliac endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.
A pubic endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.
The subdivision of the skeleton of either the pectoral or pelvic girdle.
Subdivision of skeleton consisting of all skeletal elements in an hindlimb zeugopod region. Typically consists of the tibia and the fibula.

There are three cuneiform bones in the human foot: the medial cuneiform the intermediate cuneiform also known as the middle the lateral cuneiform. They are located between the navicular bone and the first, second and third metatarsal bones and are medial to the cuboid bone[WP, unvetted, human specific].
A bone which does not occur frequently in the body but is still present in a significantly large number of organisms.

An accessory bone located proximal to the base of the fifth metatarsal. Its prevalence has been reported to be from 0.1% to 1.0%. This bone is found within the peroneus brevis tendon and is considered to be asymptomatic in the majority of people.
An accessory bone tubercle which if present lies posterior to the talus.

An accessory bone of the pes that occasionally develops abnormally in front of the ankle towards the inside of the pes. This bone may be present in approximately 2.5% of the general population and is usually asymptomatic.
A piece of bone that is located within a suture in the cranium.
An orbitosphenoid endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.
An alisphenoid endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.
An alisphenoid endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.
Endochondral tarsal bone articulating with centralia and metatarsal 4.
Endochondral tarsal bone articulating with centralia and metatarsal 5.

definition.value: We need to restrict the logical definition such that it is *only* connecting to metatarsal 5

value.value: Endochondral carpal bone similar to distal carpal 4, but lost in most reptiles and mammals.
A bone that is part of an appendage girdle complex (i.e. any bone in a limb, fin or girdle).
A bone that is part of a pectoral complex. Examples: scapula, manus phalanx, any carpal bone, any bone of the pectoral fin.
A bone that is part of a pelvic complex. Examples: pubis, ischium, fot phalanx, any tarsal bone, any bone of the pelvic fin or girdle.
The collection of all meningeal layers that line a central nervous system.
A sacral vertebra endochondral element that is composed primarily of a pre-cartilage condensation.
A sacral vertebra endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.

The extension of the ilium above the level of the acetabulum. Attachment site for both hindlimb and caudal musculature. Medially is the site of attachment of the sacral ribs, where these exist[PHENOSCAPE:ad].

The body of ilium enters into the formation of the acetabulum, of which it forms rather less than two-fifths. Its external surface is partly articular, partly non-articular; the articular segment forms part of the lunate surface of the acetabulum, the non-articular portion contributes to the acetabular fossa. The internal surface of the body is part of the wall of the lesser pelvis and gives origin to some fibers of the Obturator internus. Below, it is continuous with the pelvic surfaces of the ischium and pubis, only a faint line indicating the place of union.
A lymphoid follicle that is part of a lymph node.
The middle pharyngeal constrictor is a fanshaped muscle, smaller than the Inferior pharyngeal constrictor muscle.
A bone separating the lacrimal and frontal bones in many tetrapod skulls.

label.value: squamous part of temporal bone primordium

value.value: An exoccipital endochondral element that is composed primarily of cartilage tissue.
A secondary follicle that is located in a lymph node.
A collection of activated B cells at the center of a secondary follicle, formed after B cells become activated and migrate to the center.

definition.value: A germinal center is a specialized microenvironment formed when activated B cells enter lymphoid follicles. Germinal centers are the foci for B cell proliferation and somatic hypermutation.[GO]

value.value: The part of the secondary follicle that surrounds the germinal center.
The enmeshed group of antigen presenting cells with extensive dendritic processes in the spleen B cell follicle that present antigen to B cells during an immune response.

definition.value: The follicular dendritic cell network is often visualized by using the monoclonal antibody FDC-M2.

value.value: The eighth rib counting from the top of the rib cage down. Note that members of this class are not necessarily homologous[ncit,modified].

label.value: subdivision of organism along appendicular axis

value.value: A major subdivision of an organism that divides an organism along an axis perpedicular to the main body anterior-posterior axis. In vertebrates, this is typically a fin or limb segment. In insects, this includes segments of appendages such as antennae, as well as segments of the insect leg.

Lies on the palmar aspect of the coffin joint between the second phalanx and third phalanx. articulates closely with the distal phalanx, to which it is connected by the impar ligament of the navicular bone. The impar ligament is very strong and permits relatively little motion between the navicular bone and the distal phalanx.
The supraglenoid tubercle is a region of the scapula to which the long head of the biceps brachii muscle attaches.
